                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>At its 66th meeting on August 24, 1950, with President Truman participating, the
                    National Security Council agreed that permission to export steel rails from the
                    United States to the People’s Republic of China should be denied (<gloss
                        target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Action No. 347<hi rend="italic">e</hi>).
                    Documentation on other more general questions of East-West trade at this meeting
                    is scheduled for publication in volume IV.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
